snippet.textDisplay: This song really hits me in the feels. 7 days ago, on January 21st, 2020, my dad passed away. He was going through so much depression and he was also on drugs.. and I wasn’t home when it happened but he committed suicide, and I was devastated, my sister saw my dad lying on the floor, and I didn’t thankfully because my sister told me to stay in the car. I just still can’t believe that he’s really gone... it seemed like yesterday he was here tucking me in to bed and now... he’s not. I had to attend my first funeral that week... it was very hard... my mom is just a wreck right now... and so am I. I keep listening to this song and the lyircs, and I just think of how it really fits my situation... “Was there something I could’ve said to make your heart beat better... was there something I could’ve said to make it all stop hurting.. it kills me how your mind could make you feel so worthless...” It just brings me to tears because that’s what my dad was feeling, he was going through so much pain... he felt worthless, like nobody ever cared about him.. but he didn’t realize how much we all loved him.... he always told me that me and my siblings were the only thing keeping him going... and I wish I could’ve just talked to him..... to stop it from happening, I think to myself every day about if I could’ve stopped it. But I probably couldn’t have... he was going insane and just decided to end it all. It hurts... my dad was my best friend... my partner... and now he’s disappeared from my life... it kills me, I wish I could’ve done something.. I feel like if he listened to me... he wouldn’t have done it😭😭 but at least I know he’s in a better place now.

snippet.textDisplay:
I had a friend a few years ago. She was engaged to a wonderful guy, they were happy. A few days after they found out that Pati was pregnant, her ex-boyfriend came to Matt and shot him. Pati struggled with this situation for another month or two. I helped her as much as I could, but one day I said "I need 2 hours for myself". In the evening she didn't answer the phone. The next day I found out that she had committed suicide. At least 10 years have passed, and I still think it was my fault.
Thank you Lewis for this song. It brought back memories, but thanks to it I feel a little better. ❤️
